Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • Node

  • public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    Write a description of class Node here. Takes in the current map from the world and converts it into a graph of nodes, each with a cost of 1. The 0's from the 2d array represent the nodes. Anything else is ignored. Calculates the shortest path from a target to the source. Used to give the enemy a path to the player, while going around walls. The algorithm calculates the cost to each node in the graph starting from the target. The cost of the next node is equal to the cost of the previous node added to its own cost and so on until everything is calculated. Then, from the target, the path to the source is done by taking the path with the lowest cost. The source is then given the path and moves towards the target. Site used to write Dijkstras shortest path algorithm (pseudo code and tutorial used): https://brilliant.org/wiki/dijkstras-short-path-finder/ http://www.gitta.info/Accessibiliti/en/html/Dijkstra_learningObject1.html https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=q3yKyE19OR0 (tutorial) This version was modified from the original pseudo code to allow it to work with my maps. However, most of what was on the websites and video is still here.
